data.text: @Freeoh Should've just gone straight to the end credits!

@EloiseLoRoss I watched Winchester. And the sound was amazing and the film was not, but hooray for seeing Troy and Niels in the credits!!
And I watched Bombshell, because Hedy, duh. (Film's fine, though, but nothing remarkable).

ALFIE: Ugh, why is this film famous? Also, why isn’t this a film about Shelley Winters as a man-eater?

I also watched OUR WIFE as a prelude to John Stahl at Ritrovato. Wonderful although burning your beau's house down is extreme even for 1940s romantic comedies.
